# Kermadec Islands Act 1887Public Act1887 No 1

Date of assent6 June 1887

## Contents

[Title][0]
    
*   [Preamble][1]

[1][2] [Short Title][2]

[2][3] [Kermadec Islands to be part of the Colony of New Zealand from and after a day to be fixed by the Proclamation of the Governor][3]

---

An Act to provide that certain Islands in the South Pacific Ocean known as the Kermadec Group shall become Part of New Zealand, and subject to the Laws thereof.
    
*   #### Preamble
    
    WHEREAS by Letters Patent passed under the Great Seal of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland, and bearing date the eighteenth day of January, one thousand eight hundred and eighty-six, after reciting as is therein particularly recited, Her Majesty Queen Victoria did thereby authorize the Governor for the time being of the Colony of New Zealand, by Proclamation under his hand and the Public Seal of the said Colony, to declare that, from and after a day to be therein mentioned, certain islands belonging to Her Majesty situated in the South Pacific Ocean between the parallels of twenty-nine degrees and thirty-two degrees south latitude and the meridians of one hundred and seventy-seven degrees and one hundred and eighty degrees west longitude, and commonly known as the Kermadec Group, should be annexed to and form part of the Colony of New Zealand: And whereas by the said Letters Patent it is directed that the said Governor shall not issue any such Proclamation as aforesaid until the Legislature of the Colony of New Zealand shall have passed a law providing that the said islands shall, on the day aforesaid, become part of the said colony, and subject to the laws in force therein: Provided always that the application of the said laws to the said islands may be modified either by such Proclamation as aforesaid, or by any law or laws to be from time to time passed by the Legislature of the said colony for the government of the said islands so annexed: And whereas it is expedient that a law should be passed by the General Assembly, as the Legislature of the Colony of New Zealand, for the purpose of giving effect to the said Letters Patent:

BE IT THEREFORE ENACTED by the General Assembly of New Zealand in Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:---

##### 1 Short Title
    
*   The Short Title of this Act is The Kermadec Islands Act 1887\.

##### 2 Kermadec Islands to be part of the Colony of New Zealand from and after a day to be fixed by the Proclamation of the Governor
    
*   From and after a day mentioned in a Proclamation to be issued by the Governor pursuant to the authority contained in the hereinbefore in part recited Letters Patent, the said group of islands situated in the South Pacific Ocean, and commonly known as the Kermadec Group, shall become part of the Colony of New Zealand, and subject to the laws in force therein.



